# Kakeibo (Household Budget) Tool — Development Rules

## Scope

- Build and maintain **MoneyForward ME CSV ingestion, combining, marking, and
  month x person expense aggregation** only.
- Do not add budgeting advice, spending predictions, or investment logic.
- Keep this tool independent from the Parcel demo (`src/index3.js`) and the
  US market news tool (`src/news/**`).

## Privacy (critical)

- This is personal financial data. **Never commit real MoneyForward export
  CSVs, combined ledgers, or exported mark files to the repository.**
- `data/` is gitignored for exactly this reason — keep it that way.
- The browser app (`kakeiboApp.js`) must never send parsed data anywhere; all
  parsing/aggregation stays client-side (`fetch`/`XMLHttpRequest` calls are
  not allowed in this module).
- Tests and fixtures must use fabricated/anonymized data only, never real
  names, real account names, or real amounts from an actual export.
- Do not log full transaction contents (merchant names, memos) to the
  console in production code paths; status/error logs should stay limited to
  counts and non-sensitive metadata.

## Data model

- Core parsing/combining/aggregation logic (`csv.js`,
  `parseMoneyForwardCsv.js`, `combineTransactions.js`, `aggregate.js`,
  `ledgerCsv.js`) must stay framework-agnostic plain JS (no `fs`, no DOM) so
  it can run unchanged in both the Node CLI and the browser bundle.
- `ledgerCsv.js` is this tool's own round-trippable export format (carries
  marks alongside transaction data). Keep `buildLedgerCsv`/`parseLedgerCsv`
  in sync with each other and with `LEDGER_HEADER` — a browser reload must be
  able to fully restore state from a previously downloaded ledger CSV alone.
- Transaction identity is the MoneyForward `ID` column; dedupe and mark
  persistence must always key off of it.
- Expense aggregation must exclude: income rows (amount >= 0), transfers
  (`振替` = 1), and rows excluded from MoneyForward's own calculation
  (`計算対象` = 0). Keep this logic centralized in
  `aggregate.js#isExpenseEligible`.

## Testing

- Add/keep unit tests in `test/kakeibo/` for any change to parsing, combining
  or aggregation logic. Use `node --test`.
- Never add real personal CSVs as test fixtures; construct minimal inline
  CSV strings with made-up data instead.

## UI

- Keep the browser UI dependency-free (no frameworks) and served via Parcel
  as a separate entry point (`kakeibo.html`), not merged into `index.html`.
